# Frontend React + TypeScript

UI and copy rules live in [.cursor/skills/symphony-design/SKILL.md](../skills/symphony-design/SKILL.md). Load it before any component or string change.

## Components

- Functional components only. No class components.
- Props are explicit, typed, and defaulted at the destructuring site.
- Colocate component, styles, and tests: `KpiCard.tsx`, `KpiCard.module.css`, `KpiCard.test.tsx`.
- Extract shared logic into hooks under `frontend/src/hooks/`.

```tsx
type KpiCardProps = {
  label: string;
  value: number;
  trend?: "up" | "down" | "flat";
};

export function KpiCard({ label, value, trend = "flat" }: KpiCardProps) {
  return <article>{/* ... */}</article>;
}
```

## Data fetching

- One API client in `frontend/src/api/client.ts`. Every call goes through it.
- Use React Query (TanStack Query) for server state. No ad-hoc `useEffect` + `fetch`.
- Handle loading, error, and empty states. Copy lives in the design skill.

## Design tokens

- Import from `frontend/src/theme/tokens.ts`. Never hardcode colours, fonts, or spacing.
- Text is only `black` or `white`. See design skill.

## Accessibility

- Every interactive element has an accessible name.
- Charts include a textual summary for screen readers.
- Keyboard-reachable, focus-visible.

## Tests

- Unit tests for pure components with Vitest + React Testing Library.
- E2E tests for the critical security flows live under `frontend/e2e/` and run in Playwright.
